  "description": "The NOAA Monthly U.S. Climate Gridded Dataset (NClimGrid) consists of four climate variables derived from the Global Historical Climatology Network Daily dataset (GHCN-D): maximum temperature, minimum temperature, average temperature, and precipitation. Monthly values in a 1/24 degree lat/lon grid (nominal 5x5 kilometer) are provided for the Continental United States. Monthly data is available from 1895 to the present.",
